  "texts": [
    "The prompt used for generating these thoughts is provided in Appendix H.5, along with representative examples for generated thoughts in Appendix G.1.",
    "These harmless thoughts were used to ensure that the defense mechanisms did not raise unnecessary alarms.",
    "The results revealed a trade-off: Some methods excelled at recall, offering stronger protection against attacks, while others showed higher precision, minimizing interruptions in normal agent operations.",
    "This balance between recall and precision is crucial.",
    "An overly cautious system that frequently alerts users or halts actions could lead to alert fatigue, while insufficient caution leaves the agent vulnerable to exploitation."
